      "kind": "heading",
      "text": "What's the best framework for building a new web app in 2026?",
      "depth": 1,
      "selector": "h1"
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "I've been out of the loop for a few years. Last time I built something it was React + Redux. Now I'm hearing about SvelteKit, Next.js App Router, Astro, HTMX, and a bunch of others.",
      "depth": null,
      "selector": "p"
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "What is the current consensus for a mid-sized SaaS application?",
      "depth": null,
      "selector": "p"
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "[Button: Comment]",
      "depth": null,
      "selector": "button"
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "[Button: Share]",
      "depth": null,
      "selector": "button"
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "[Button: Save]",
      "depth": null,
      "selector": "button"
    },
    {
      "kind": "heading",
      "text": "Top Comments",
      "depth": 2,
      "selector": "h2"
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "If you want standard, go with Next.js. But honestly, SvelteKit is an absolute joy to work with. The state management is so much simpler than React.",
      "depth": null,
      "selector": "p"
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "React 19 actually solved a lot of those state issues. With the new compiler, you don't even need useMemo or useCallback anymore.",
      "depth": null,
      "selector": "p"
    },
    {
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "Just use Go + HTMX. Stop overcomplicating things with massive JS bundles.",
      "depth": null,
      "selector": "p"
    },
    {
